#### LXC ABOUT #####
LXC is a userspace interface for the Linux kernel containment features. Through a powerful API and simple tools, it lets Linux users easily create and manage system or application containers.


#### Instalação dos containers ####
https://github.com/buzz66boy/ns3-lxc/wiki/Install-&-Run-ns3-lxc

- Install:
	sudo apt install libyaml-cpp-dev lxc lxc-dev cmake gcc
- Create VMs: 
	cd ns-allinone-3.26/ns-3.26
	sudo lxc-create -n left -t ubuntu -f src/tap-bridge/examples/lxc-left.conf
	sudo lxc-create -n right -t ubuntu -f src/tap-bridge/example/lxc-right.conf

- Add bridge to transmit packets: 
	sudo brctl addbr br-left
	sudo brctl addbr br-right

- Create tap devices that will be used to get packet from the bridges into its process:
	sudo apt install uml-utilities
	sudo tunctl -t tap-left
	sudo tunctl -t tap-right

- Set IP addresses of the tap devices and turn them on:
	sudo ifconfig tap-left 0.0.0.0 promisc up
	sudo ifconfig tap-right 0.0.0.0 promisc up

- Add the tap devices to bridges and bring up:
	sudo brctl addif br-left tap-left
	sudo ifconfig br-left up 
	sudo brctl addif br-right tap-right
	sudo ifconfig br-right up

- Show if containers was created:
	sudo brctl show
	sudo lxc-ls -f	

- LXC requires the cgroups filesystem to be mount. So:
	sudo mount -t cgroup cgroup /sys/fs/cgroup 
  You also could add a line in /etc/fstab to do this.

- A cgroup related erro is likely to appear, so install this package:
	sudo apt install cgroup-lite

-Access the Internet in a container
	In directory "/var/lib/lxc/left" in file "config" need to change lxc.network.link = br-left to lxc.network.link = lxcbr0

-Configuring container right's "config" file... It will has the "Network Configuration" field empty
	In directory "/var/lib/lxc/right" in file "config" need to copy the same variables and assigns of container left,
	but the variable "lxc.network.ipv4" will has different ipv4 compare to container left. Example: 
	lxc.network.ipv4 = 10.0.0.2/24 
	
- Start the container:
	sudo lxc-start -n left
	sudo lxc-start -n right
	
- Access the container
	sudo lxc-attach -n left
	sudo lxc-attach -n right

 #INSIDE OF THE CONTAINER LEFT#
 - Usuário: ubuntu
   Senha: ubuntu
 - Install:
	sudo apt-get install software-properties-common
	sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ubuntu-toolchain-r/test
	sudo apt update
	sudo apt install gcc-4.9
	sudo apt install g++-4.9
	sudo apt install libpcre3 libpcre3-dev
	sudo apt install libssl-dev
	sudo apt install checkinstall
	
 #INSIDE OF THE LEFT CONTAINER/SERVER#	
- HTTP Server
- Get wget:
	sudo apt-get install wget

- Get nginx
	wget http://nginx.org/download/nginx-1.9.12.tar.gz

- Unpack
	tar xzvf nginx-1.9.12.tar.gz

- Install
	cd nginx-1.9.12
	./configure
	make
	sudo checkinstall

- Requirements for the installation of the Dash.js (Multimedia Player)
- Install cURL
	sudo apt-get install curl

- Install Node.js
	curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_9.x | sudo -E bash -
	sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

- Install grunt
	npm install -g grunt-cli
	npm install grunt-template-jasmine-istanbul --save-dev

- Install also
	npm install grunt-contrib-connect grunt-contrib-watch grunt-contrib-jshint grunt-contrib-uglify

- And now download and unzip Dash player:
	wget https://github.com/Dash-Industry-Forum/dash.js/archive/development.zip
	unzip development.zip

 #INSIDE OF THE RIGHT CONTAINER/CLIENT#
  	- apt-get install python-pip
	
	- apt-get install python-dev libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev zlib1g-dev
	
	- apt-get install git-all

	- git clone https://github.com/broadbent/scootplayer.git

	- cd scootplayer/

 	- pip install -r requirements.txt
